  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The enlargement of the rear dormer extension by virtue of the resulting adverse increase in bulk and visibility from surrounding streets both in short and long views would will have a negative effect on the architectural integrity of the property and the unity of the terrace causing significant harm to the the street scene and the character and appearance of the New River Conservation Area.  The proposal is contrary to PPS5, policies: D1; D4; D11; D24 and D25 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002, the Islington Urban Design Guide and the Conservation Area Design Guidelines."
